  "poem": {
    "content": "The network hums a dizzy tune,\na jungle rhythm, skin so soon\nto feel the oil, the grit, the stain,\nlike laundry piled in sun and rain.\n\nA budget stretched, a level low,\nwhere dreams like envelopes all go,\naddressed to hopes that never land,\ncarried by a goose across the sand.\n\nThe library sleeps, a silent treat,\nwhile credit dwindles, bitter, sweet.\nA flag unfurls, a hopeful sign,\nbut shadows lengthen, intertwine.\n\nThe world spins fast, delirium's hold,\na story whispered, bought and sold.\nFind solace in the rustling leaves,\nwhere wild abandon interweaves.\n\nA painted vista, stark and grand,\nupon this lonely, barren land.\nA twisted path, a bitter chase,\na fleeting moment, time and space.",
